{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/median-shortest-distance-sum/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Mindscape"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"feccd663-f7db-5d37-a2e6-95da16280f9a","excerpt":"So while LeetCoding, I encountered problems like 296. Best Meeting Point where you use the fact that median gives you the shortest sum of distance from other…","html":"<p>So while LeetCoding, I encountered problems like <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/best-meeting-point/\">296. Best Meeting Point</a> where you use the fact that median gives you the shortest sum of distance from other nodes to it. And I am going to show your why, without boring math equations.</p>\n<h2>Graph time</h2>\n<p>Suppose we have a 1D axis, and a bunch of points on it: (Sorry about the M$ Paint quality)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/ad6c47c70b787be573cae2b52bc0016e/e17e5/1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.83783783783784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img1\"\n        title=\"img1\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/ad6c47c70b787be573cae2b52bc0016e/e17e5/1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/ad6c47c70b787be573cae2b52bc0016e/12f09/1.png 148w,\n/blog/static/ad6c47c70b787be573cae2b52bc0016e/e4a3f/1.png 295w,\n/blog/static/ad6c47c70b787be573cae2b52bc0016e/e17e5/1.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>We randomly pick a point <code class=\"language-text\">x</code> on this axis to see if this is the best point with the minimal sum of distance to other points. And lets say there are <code class=\"language-text\">m</code> points to the left of <code class=\"language-text\">x</code>, and <code class=\"language-text\">n</code> points to the right of <code class=\"language-text\">x</code>.</p>\n<h2>Let’s try to minimize the sum</h2>\n<p>What would happen to the sum of distance if we move <code class=\"language-text\">x</code> to the right by 1 unit?</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/e33bee55a8de2513576fd451a0f7f376/e17e5/2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.45945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img2\"\n        title=\"img2\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/e33bee55a8de2513576fd451a0f7f376/e17e5/2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/e33bee55a8de2513576fd451a0f7f376/12f09/2.png 148w,\n/blog/static/e33bee55a8de2513576fd451a0f7f376/e4a3f/2.png 295w,\n/blog/static/e33bee55a8de2513576fd451a0f7f376/e17e5/2.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Well, since we are 1 unit further away from all of the <code class=\"language-text\">m</code> points on the left, the sum increase by <code class=\"language-text\">m</code>. And since we are 1 unit closer to all of the <code class=\"language-text\">n</code> points on the right, the sum also decrease by <code class=\"language-text\">n</code>. In other words: <code class=\"language-text\">new_sum = old_sum + m - n</code>.</p>\n<p>Apparently, if there are more points on the right than these on the left, we should keep moving to the right to minimize the sum.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/e4f2b9d661fedd557a1ddb071e120ddf/e17e5/3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.70270270270271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img3\"\n        title=\"img3\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/e4f2b9d661fedd557a1ddb071e120ddf/e17e5/3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/e4f2b9d661fedd557a1ddb071e120ddf/12f09/3.png 148w,\n/blog/static/e4f2b9d661fedd557a1ddb071e120ddf/e4a3f/3.png 295w,\n/blog/static/e4f2b9d661fedd557a1ddb071e120ddf/e17e5/3.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>And we’ve reached median</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/3e70a21aad125794c06a8fa9c2d9fa0f/e17e5/4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.78378378378378%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img4\"\n        title=\"img4\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/3e70a21aad125794c06a8fa9c2d9fa0f/e17e5/4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/3e70a21aad125794c06a8fa9c2d9fa0f/12f09/4.png 148w,\n/blog/static/3e70a21aad125794c06a8fa9c2d9fa0f/e4a3f/4.png 295w,\n/blog/static/3e70a21aad125794c06a8fa9c2d9fa0f/e17e5/4.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>But when do we stop moving? Thats where <code class=\"language-text\">m == n</code>, i.e, there are equal number of points on either left or right. Because <code class=\"language-text\">m - n == 0</code> and we can’t decrease the sum any further. And this point, is the median (because thats the definition of median: <em>The median is the value separating the higher half from the lower half of a data sample</em>)</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Illustration - why median gives shortest sum of distance?","date":"October 05, 2019","category":"note"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/median-shortest-distance-sum/"}}}